Sentencas: Ni1 - xFex bimetallic-based cermet anodes were investigated for hydrocarbon-fueled solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Ni1-xFex-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuel

Sentencas: Ni-1 (-) Fe-x(x)-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 cermet anodes were synthesized using a glycine nitrate process, and their electrical conductivity and the amount of carbon deposits were found to decrease with increasing Fe content.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Ni1-xFex-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuel

Sentencas: The anode polarization resistance for the CH4 fuel was significantly reduced by Fe alloying, which was strongly related to the carbon deposition behavior.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Ni1-xFex-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuel

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the single cell with Ni0.85Fe0.15-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 in CH4 at 800 degrees C was 0.27 W/cm(2).
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Ni1-xFex-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuel

Sentencas: Fe alloying significantly improved the electrochemical performance of solid oxide fuel cells in CH4 fuel by suppressing carbon deposition.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Ni1-xFex-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuel
